<p class="fd-paragraph">
  A structured task layer that captures every action item generated by agents, workflows, or staff — with priority scoring, assignment logic, and completion tracking built in. Nothing falls through the cracks.
</p>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">What it does</h2>
<ul class="fd-list">
  <li class="fd-list-item">Centralized task inbox across all sources: agents, workflows, manual creation</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Priority scoring based on acuity, due date, and patient risk</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Assignment rules route tasks to the right staff or agent automatically</li>
  <li class="fd-list-item">Completion tracking with timestamps, notes, and outcome documentation</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="fd-section-heading">The foundation for agentic work</h2>
<p class="fd-paragraph">
  Tasks is the operational backbone of Machina. Every agent action, every workflow step, every staff interaction is captured as a task — creating a complete, auditable record of care operations.
</p>
